line_1: Why all this art, this labour'd ornament;
line_2: To captivate, you'll cry no doubt, 'tis meant.
She seemed on change and novel grace intent,
'Till that large Stock of Sap is spent,

line_1: To own 'tis my Delight as well as Ornament.
line_2: Charm'd by your Art, I generously consent,
Spun the soft silk, and spread the various teint:
The gilded insect's colours yet were feint
Our grannums thus with diff'rent dies besprent,
